The Ebonyi State Government has commended President Muhammadu Buhari for his two-day official working visit to the state. Gov. David Umahi on Sunday, expressed “deep gratitude” over the visit in Abakaliki. The President had on May 5 and 6, visited the state for commissioning of projects, including King David University of Medical Science and Technology. Others included the University Flyover, dualised concrete road, Presidential Lounge of the state International Airport. Umahi described Buhari’s presence in the state for all the projects commissioned as “generous”. “We are pleased to convey to you the warm appreciation of Ebonyi people and the South-East, over your positive dispositions to the development of the zone. “While we assure your Excellency of our unwavering support and solidarity, please accept always, the assurances of the esteemed regards and best wishes of the Government and Ebonyi people,” Umahi said.